    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Monster Hunter's Handbook pg. 26</em><br/><strong>Price</strong> 90 gp; <strong>Weight</strong> 1 lb.<br/><strong>Category</strong> Adventuring Gear</p><h2 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbolN.gif\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\" title=\"A character cannot select from the humanoid type, subtypes, or varieties.\"/>Description</h2><p>These books detail common behavior patterns and special abilities of a particular creature type. When used as a reference (an action that typically requires 1d4 minutes of searching the text), a hunter's manual grants a +2 circumstance bonus on Knowledge checks to learn about special abilities and weaknesses of the text's associated creature type for 1 hour.<br/><br/> If the reader successfully makes such a Knowledge check using the book, she gains a +1 circumstance bonus on her next saving throw against any of that creature's spell-like, supernatural, or extraordinary abilities she identified.</p>",
